rComments: TAKE STAT 100 INSTEAD!!!!!! do not take econ 202 with her, shes a good enough teacher but her class is 90% tests and the tests are hard. Stat 100 covers the same credit and its 10x easier. Schultz is actually a good teacher  but she makes her class impossible to get a good grade in, save yourself the time and effort and dont take it.

Colleen does a poor job on accurately testing students for the subject matter learned in class. She generally carries herself with a poor attitude in class, and seems to be irritated when students ask questions. She does not appear to be passionate about teaching.

Worst professor I had so far at UIUC. Tricky exam questions and unhelpful TA sections. The final is not fair, and the questions are not hard, but very confusing. Whatever, you can not avoid her since only she teaches econ202 for years. Bear with it!

Colleen is the worst professor I've had at U of I. She tries to trick you with her exams and makes statistics much more difficult than it has to be.  I learned more by myself than from her. It's a shame that this course is required for business majors.

Quite horrible professor. You need to be in class as much of the material is out of order or not presented in the book in the same manner that is presented in class. She also uses the iClicker system for points every class period. She will try to play tricks on exams, and doesn't allow audio recording. Doesn't post answers to PP slides if you miss.
Although she can be crabby and boring she is amazing at explaining things clearly.  Go to class, pay attention, and you'll get a good grade.  Her grading policy is very student friendly and fair.

The class itself was average as far as difficulty. The best way to learn the material is by going to lecture. The tests can be a bit tricky. I don't know if this is typical or if I just got lucky but at the end of the semester she pretty much threw points out for free to the whole class. Overall she's alright.

I hate this professor.. She was awful and her tests were the trickiest test I've ever seen. Horribly boring lectures. She is extremely sarcastic when you go to her for help. Avoid her at all costs. She is terrible

While the material itself is really easy, Schultz makes the exams as tricky as possible. Class is pretty boring, but can be helpful. The final was optional which was nice. Overall, it is very easy to get a B, but don't expect an A without a lot of studying, despite the easiness of the material.

Exams may be tricky, but they aren't terrible as long as you attend lectures and do all the homework. You should make sure you understand all the homework problems and the trickiest problems because they will always appear on exams. Easy A or B. Anything less is because you didn't understand all the concepts taught or in the homework.
Some questions in the exams are tricky. But generally the class is easy. The professor is kind of lazy.

Agree with below. This is an easy A class if you pay attention to in-class problems and do your hw. The in-class problems and practice tests resemble the actual tests, so just learn them well and you'll do great. On one of our midterms, 30% got perfect scores. Yes, seriously.
just not a fun person at all. no technology allowed in class, no laptops no phones out, can't use camera phone to take picture of a PP slide.

Seems like a bitter person. Also, she kept saying the hw is due wednesday but not the time. Turns out its due wednesday morning at 5 am hahahaha. I had not paid for the program yet as i registered for the course late. TA says she repeated the time many times which she did NOT.No lowest score drop policy so she is basically out to make life hell.
Her class is challenging, no doubt about it. Go to class everyday, pay attention and take good notes. Her exams can be hard, but if you study beforehand, you won't have a problem.

Relatively straightforward and helpful. I had a few questions and she was good about responding in a timely manner. My TA was also very helpful. She has clear and reasonable expectations, should not be too difficult if you are willing to put in the effort.
This professor is extremely tricky!!! I've been to the TA office hours and even the TAs can't solve her questions sometimes.
The class is a complete joke, but she is literally the WORST professor I've had on campus. She will definitely try to trick you on exams so be super careful when reading each question.

She has a very weird calculator policy, you can only use the 1$ basic calculator. She uses numbers with 6 decimals in her problems to her delight) and you have to do all the calculations with that calculator so if you hit a wrong button by mistake, you have to start all over. I hated every second of her class: useless, boring and uninteresting.

She at times seems uninterested, there are many tricks put on the test so make sure to review things from past exams because that always has a large enough impact on the following tests, the tests are not curved but the class is, if you put in the work to understand the material, you should do well.
